vtdec: list IOSurface caps before plain SystemMemory in the src template

Decoder template order decides the negotiated memory type through playbin:
playsink's convert bin answers vtdec's caps query by intersecting FILTER-first
(gstplaysinkconvertbin.c FILTER_CAPS), i.e. the result is ordered by vtdec's own
template, and gst_vtdec_negotiate() then gst_caps_truncate()s to structure 0.
With plain SystemMemory listed before memory:IOSurface, the CPU-readback path
always wins even when the sink prefers (and lists first) IOSurface caps.

Reordering the template mirrors how the va* decoders get zero-copy on Linux
(their templates list VAMemory/DMABuf before raw SystemMemory), and lets
IOSurface negotiate through playsink WITHOUT the native-video flag - which
would disable subtitleoverlay and with it all subtitle rendering. Sinks that
don't support memory:IOSurface are unaffected: the intersection just falls
through to the SystemMemory structures. GLMemory stays first, so texture-cache
consumers (glimagesink) are unaffected too.

diff --git a/subprojects/gst-plugins-bad/sys/applemedia/vtdec.c b/subprojects/gst-plugins-bad/sys/applemedia/vtdec.c
--- a/subprojects/gst-plugins-bad/sys/applemedia/vtdec.c
+++ b/subprojects/gst-plugins-bad/sys/applemedia/vtdec.c
@@ -258,12 +258,12 @@
 #define VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_GL_FORMATS "{ NV12 }"
 #define VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_VULKAN_FORMATS "{ NV12, BGRA }"
 
 #define VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_NATIVE                                           \
     GST_VIDEO_CAPS_MAKE_WITH_FEATURES(GST_CAPS_FEATURE_MEMORY_GL_MEMORY,\
         VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_GL_FORMATS) ", "                                 \
     "texture-target = (string) rectangle ;"                              \
-    GST_VIDEO_CAPS_MAKE(VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_NATIVE_FORMATS) ";"              \
     GST_VIDEO_CAPS_MAKE_WITH_FEATURES(GST_CAPS_FEATURE_MEMORY_IOSURFACE,\
-        VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_NATIVE_FORMATS)
+        VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_NATIVE_FORMATS) ";"                              \
+    GST_VIDEO_CAPS_MAKE(VIDEO_SRC_CAPS_NATIVE_FORMATS)
 
 #ifdef APPLEMEDIA_MOLTENVK
